modules.description: Provides compression and decompression functions for byte sequences using the zlib library. Works with input and output buffers, handling raw and compressed data formats. Used to reduce file size during data transmission or storage and to restore original data from compressed streams.

This module offers compression and decompression functionalities using the deflate algorithm, supporting both zlib and gzip formats with customizable parameters. It operates on bigarrays and byte sequences, enabling efficient handling of large data streams while managing stateful processes and checksums. Use cases include optimizing network transmission, file compression, and scenarios requiring concurrent OCaml thread execution during I/O operations.
